      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match simulated boundary conditions within documented tolerances; fluid temperature, hematocrit, and flow rate deviations must be reported.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments used bovine blood at 37 ± 0.5 °C with hematocrit 33 ± 1%. Flow rates were controlled to ±0.1 L/min. CFD boundary conditions were set to nominal experimental values; sensitivity of RHI to ±1% hematocrit variation was assessed and found negligible (<0.8% RHI change)."
    },
