      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must cover the COU operating envelope (2400–3200 RPM, 2–6 L/min) and use a geometrically equivalent pump model.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry used in the COU simulations. The 5 validation operating points span the COU envelope corners and centroid. Geometric fidelity confirmed by CMM measurement of the physical test article against the CAD model (deviations < 0.05 mm)."
